{"article_id":"06MNeUhpAQySKVbS","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"DALLAS -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"A health care worker","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"who cared for the Ebola patient","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"who died last week","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"tested positive for the deadly virus ,","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"sending health officials scrambling Sunday to find the `` breach in protocol ''","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"that resulted in her infection .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"The woman was among caregivers for Thomas Eric Duncan ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"who died Wednesday at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"A state test","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"finding","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"that she had Ebola","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"was confirmed Sunday by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"making it the first known case","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"transmitted in the U.S .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"CDC chief Thomas Frieden said","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"his agency will investigate","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"how a worker in full protective gear contracted the virus .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"`` At some point there was a breach in protocol , ''","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Frieden said .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"`` That breach in protocol resulted in this infection . ''","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"The White House said","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"President Obama discussed the news with Health and Human Services Secretary Sylvia Burwell ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"directing","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"that the CDC `` investigation into the apparent breach in infection-control protocols at the Dallas hospital move as expeditiously","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"as possible . ''","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Dallas Police officers stood sentry outside the two-story beige-brick apartment building Sunday in the leafy East Dallas neighborhood","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"where the patient lived .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Across the street , a scrum of news media lined up along the curb .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"A few neighbors wandered over","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"to survey the scene .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Lynda Edwards ,","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"who lives down the street ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"she became alarmed","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"when helicopters began hovering overhead around 7 a.m.","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"and news crews began arriving .","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"`` It 's scary , ''","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"she said ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"that televised news conferences from the CDC have n't eased her fears .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` It does n't sound like we have a plan , ''","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Edwards said .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"`` The public needs to know","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"what the plan is . ''","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"The phone call from the CDC of the Ebola confirmation reached Dallas Mayor Mike Rawlings around midnight Saturday ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"triggering a new round of decontamination and new steps","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"to reassure residents .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"`` I was disappointed","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"but not surprised , ''","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"Rawlings told .","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"`` The odds were we would have another one . ''","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"For the next seven hours , members of the Dallas Fire-Rescue Department descended on the apartment building","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"where the infected medical worker lived","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"and decontaminated everything outside and in the common areas of the building , including the laundry room , entrance way , elevator and hallways ,","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"They did not enter the worker 's apartment .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"As workers in hazmat suits scrubbed nearby ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"Rawlings personally walked through the neighborhood ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"talking to residents .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"As a precaution , the workers were ordered to do a second cleaning of all common areas .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"`` We knew","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"the patient was being taken care of at the hospital , ''","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"Rawlings said .","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"`` We focused on the safety of the city . ''","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"City and county officials ,","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"who are heading the response effort ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"will be increasing the number of people","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"monitored by CDC staffers in Dallas ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"Rawlings said .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"At least 19 hospital staffers","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"who dealt with Duncan during his two hospital visits","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"were monitoring themselves for signs of Ebola .","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"Now that group will be closely monitored by the CDC team ,","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"which includes taking their temperature twice a day , daily visits by CDC staff and restrictions on their movement ,","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"`` This shows","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"the system 's working , ''","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"Rawlings said .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"`` That 's what 's making me feel most comfortable . ''","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Rawlings said","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"the patient 's dog ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"still inside the apartment ,","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"will soon be sent to a new location","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"to await a reunion with its owner .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"There were no plans","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"to euthanize the dog","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"as Spanish officials did in a case last week ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"The Ebola epidemic has killed more than 4,000 people in West Africa , the vast majority of them in Liberia , Guinea and Sierra Leone .","depth":4},{"id":90,"text":"In the U.S. , tougher scrutiny for Ebola began Saturday at New York 's Kennedy Airport ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"where federal Homeland Security officials began screening travelers from those nations ,","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"taking their temperature","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"and observing them for other Ebola symptoms .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"The program will be added at four more U.S. airports in coming days .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"Rep. Michael McCaul , R-Texas , said","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"more action might be needed .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"`` There 's a lot of talk","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"about banning flights , ''","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"McCaul said on CBS ' Face the Nation .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"`` I think","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"we need to ... look at the idea","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"of potentially temporarily suspending the 13,000 visas","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"that would be coming out of this region . ''","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"Sen. John McCain , R-Ariz. ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"speaking on CNN 's State of the Union ,","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"the U.S. needs `` some kind of czar ''","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"to take charge of the Ebola response .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"`` Americans have to be reassured , ''","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"The Dallas caregiver reported having a fever Friday night","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"and was hospitalized , isolated","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"and referred for testing within 90 minutes ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"Clay Jenkins , Dallas County 's chief executive and its Homeland Security director , said at a news conference .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"`` While this is obviously bad news ,","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"it is not news","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"that should bring about panic , ''","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"Jenkins said .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"`` We knew","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"it was a possibility","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"that a second person would contract the virus .","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"We had a contingency plan in place . ''","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"The woman ,","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"who requested anonymity ,","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"was listed in stable condition ,","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"Jenkins said .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"Frieden cited four steps","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"being taken by the CDC :","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"ensuring the woman is cared for safely ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"identifying her contacts ,","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"treating all health care workers","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"who cared for Duncan","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"as having potentially been exposed ,","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"and reviewing procedures","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"used to protect health care workers","depth":16},{"id":136,"text":"who treat Ebola patients .","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"Frieden called the positive test `` very concerning ''","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"but stressed","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"that the protocols for the care of Ebola patients are safe","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"if done properly .","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"that removing the protective gear incorrectly , for example , raises risk .","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"The news hit the region 's health care community hard ,","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"said Steve Love , president and chief executive of the Dallas-Fort Worth Hospital Council .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"The area 's 85 hospitals have been training constantly for an Ebola case","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"and holding conference calls","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"to discuss such things","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"as what to do","depth":16},{"id":149,"text":"if a child with Ebola shows up at an emergency room ,","depth":16},{"id":150,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"`` We were hoping and praying","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"there would not be any additional Ebola cases , ''","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"Love said .","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"`` But it is not surprising that this happened . ''","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"Dan Varga , chief clinical officer for the hospital group","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"that includes Texas Health Presbyterian ,","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"confirmed","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"that the woman had worn full protective gear","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"when working with Duncan .","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"the woman was not one of the 48 health care workers","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"who were being most closely watched","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"and that the number of workers","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"being monitored","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"could be expanded .","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"Duncan initially sought treatment Sept. 25","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"and was sent home with antibiotics ,","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"despite informing health workers","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"he had recently been to West Africa .","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"He returned three days later in an ambulance","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"and was diagnosed with the deadly infection .","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"Duncan was the first person","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"diagnosed with Ebola in the U.S .","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"Ebola is spread through direct contact with bodily fluids of a sick person or exposure to contaminated objects such as needles .","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"People are not contagious","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"before symptoms such as fever develop .","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"The health care worker","depth":18},{"id":178,"text":"who tested positive ,","depth":18},{"id":179,"text":"along with the others","depth":19},{"id":180,"text":"who dealt with Duncan ,","depth":19},{"id":181,"text":"was self-monitoring","depth":18},{"id":182,"text":"- watching for symptoms consistent with early signs of Ebola ,","depth":16},{"id":183,"text":"Varga said .","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"The monitoring guidelines include taking a temperature twice a day .","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"`` That health care worker is a heroic person , ''","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"Jenkins said .","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"`` Let 's remember","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"as we do our work","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"that this is a real person","depth":15},{"id":190,"text":"who is going through a great ordeal ,","depth":15},{"id":191,"text":"and so is that person 's family . ''","depth":14},{"id":192,"text":"Last week , the hospital defended the quality of care","depth":8},{"id":193,"text":"it provided Duncan ,","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":195,"text":"treatment was not affected by the man 's nationality or lack of health insurance .","depth":8},{"id":196,"text":"`` Our care team provided Mr. Duncan with the same high level of attention and care","depth":8},{"id":197,"text":"that would be given any patient ,","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"regardless of nationality or ability","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"to pay for care , ''","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"said Wendell Watson , the hospital 's director of public relations , in a statement .","depth":7},{"id":201,"text":"Bacon reported from McLean , Va .","depth":3},{"id":202,"text":"Contributing 